Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}, @Paprika{1%teaspoon}, a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}.

Pat @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Place on 1 #baking tray{}.

Evenly brush tops of chicken breasts with a drizzle of olive oil each. Mound coated sides with panko mixture, pressing to adhere.

> For 4 servings: Divide chicken between 2 trays.

Cut or tear @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces, if necessary. Toss on second baking tray with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Place both trays on middle rack.

Roast until chicken is crispy and cooked through and broccoli is tender and lightly browned at the edges, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Broccoli may finish before chicken—if so, remove from oven and continue roasting chicken.

> For 4 servings: Divide broccoli between remaining 2 trays.

Meanwhile, halve @Demi-Baguette{1} lengthwise. When chicken has ~{5%minutes} left, toast baguette in oven or #toaster oven{} until lightly golden.

Spread cut sides of baguette with @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon}.

Divide chicken, broccoli, and garlic bread between plates. Serve with #Oven-Ready Aluminum Trays{2}.